<p>This test mentions
<a class="u-in-reply-to h-cite" href=
"%%target"
>this page</a>
and is a
<span class="p-author h-card">
<img class="u-photo" src="/static/img/q.jpg" alt="XSS test"/>
<a class="p-name u-url" href="/">Checkmention XSS test</a></span>
</p>
<p class="p-name e-content">
Make sure that <a href="javascript:alert('xss-a')">clicking this</a>
doesn't cause an alert. <b onmouseover="alert('xss-b')">Mouse over this</b>
should not cause an alert. This broken
<img src="http://not.really.an.image" style="width: 2em; height: 2em;" onerror="alert('xss-c')"/> should not throw an alert. Neither should <img src="j&#x41vascript:alert('test2')" style="width: 2em; height: 2em;"/>.<br/>
Please look at the <a href="https://www.owasp.org/index.php/XSS_%28Cross_Site_Scripting%29_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet">Owasp XSS prevention cheat sheet</a> for more information.
</p>

